<L>__{interior grandma's car day}
<A>__{tj's in the passenger seat. his dad drives. they sit in silence for a little while. then dad speaks }
<C>__{dad}
<D>__{did you do it?}
<A>__{tj pauses before answering.}
<C>__{tj}
<D>__{not really.}
<C>__{dad}
<D>__{not really?}
<C>__{tj}
<D>__{i didn't do it.}
<C>__{dad}
<D>__{what does `not really' mean?}
<A>__{tj ignores him, stares out the car window.}
<C>__{dad }
<D>__{tell me what `not really' means.}
<C>__{tj}
<D>__{it means i didn't do it.}
<C>__{dad}
<D>__{no, it doesn't. why would you say 'not really'?}
<C>__{tj}
<D>__{i didn't.}
<C>__{dad}
<D>__{you did. i heard you.}
<C>__{tj}
<D>__{i said i didn't do it.}
<C>__{dad}
<D>__{yeah, before that. i asked if you did it. you said `not really'.}
<C>__{tj}
<D>__{i can't remember what i said.}
<C>__{dad}
<D>__{why would you do something like that?}
<A>__{dad pulls the car into the driveway and comes to an abrupt stop. hesher is sitting in a lawn chair in the middle of the driveway, sunbathing with his shirt off, drinking beer. he has a farmer's tan. tj jumps out. dad stares at hesher from inside the car.}
<C>__{hesher}
<D>__{howdy.}
<A>__{tj walks past hesher without looking at him.}
